Package: SentimentAnalyzer
Type: Package
Title: Sentiment Analysis Tools for Textual Reviews
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Amanda Winata <Amanda.Winata@campus.lmu.de>
Maintainer: Amanda Winata <Amanda.Winata@campus.lmu.de>
Description: SentimentAnalyzer provides tools to assess and analyze sentiment in textual data,
    using simple lexical analysis methods. It can calculate, summarize, and classify sentiments
    in text data without needing external dependencies, making it suitable for educational
    purposes and lightweight applictions. Note: While this package is licensed under the MIT License, 
    it is intended primarily for academic use and was developed as a university homework.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 2.1.0)
